From Example [ex:implicit-circle], we have $\deriv{y}{x} = -\dfrac{x}{y}$.

Differentiate again using the Quotient Rule:
$$
 \dderiv{y}{x} 
 &= \deriv{}{x}\left[-\frac{x}{y}\right]
 = -\frac{y \cdot 1 - x \cdot \deriv{y}{x}}{y^{2}} \\[8pt]
 &= -\frac{y - x\left(-\frac{x}{y}\right)}{y^{2}}
 = -\frac{y + \frac{x^{2}}{y}}{y^{2}} \\[8pt]
 &= -\frac{\frac{y^{2} + x^{2}}{y}}{y^{2}}
 = -\frac{x^{2} + y^{2}}{y^{3}}
 = -\frac{25}{y^{3}}.
$$
In the last step, we used $x^{2} + y^{2} = 25$.
